# Example secret file for `act` runner
# Copy to `.github/act.secrets` (or pass via --secret-file) and fill with real values.
# Keep this file out of source control for real secrets; this is only an example.
#
# Only include secrets actually referenced by workflows to avoid confusion.

## GitHub token (required by most workflows)
# Minimal scope: repo
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

## NPM token for publishing (used as NODE_AUTH_TOKEN)
# Scope: publish to the npm registry for packages in this repo
NPM_TOKEN=npm_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

## Chromatic project token for Storybook publishing
CHROMATIC_PROJECT_TOKEN=chpt_XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX

## Optional: add others as KEY=VALUE if you wire new workflows
# DOCKERHUB_TOKEN=

